@startuml
title Final Project - Role-Based Access Control Diagram

left to right direction
hide circle

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial

skinparam Class {
  BorderColor #334155
  BackgroundColor white
  FontColor #0F172A
}

skinparam Arrow {
  Color #475569
  Thickness 1
}

skinparam Note {
  BackgroundColor #F8FAFC
  BorderColor #CBD5E1
  FontColor #334155
}

class User {
  +id: bigint
  +name: string
  +email: string
  +requested_role: string
  +approved_at: datetime

  --
  +assignRole()
  +removeRole()
  +hasRole()
  +can()
}

class Role {
  +id: bigint
  +name: string
  +guard_name: string

  --
  +givePermissionTo()
  +revokePermissionTo()
}

class Permission {
  +id: bigint
  +name: string
  +guard_name: string
}

User "0..*" -- "0..*" Role : assigned roles
Role "0..*" -- "0..*" Permission : grants permissions
User ..> Permission : checked through roles

note bottom of User
All authenticated actors are stored
as User records.

Student, Teacher, Parent, Secretary,
and Administrator are represented
through assigned roles.
end note

note right of Role
Roles define the main access level
of each user and group permissions
related to system features.
end note

note bottom of Permission
Permissions control access to
specific actions such as managing
users, courses, timetables,
payments, and resources.
end note

@enduml